I wouldn't have
to speak so much.

00:12:03.114 --> 00:12:04.530
GOPI KALLAYIL:
Repetition is good.

00:12:04.530 --> 00:12:05.710
So I have two questions
for you, Shilpa.

00:12:05.710 --> 00:12:06.250
SHILPA SHETTY KUNDRA: Yeah.

00:12:06.250 --> 00:12:07.740
GOPI KALLAYIL: First is, how
has the experience with YouTube

00:12:07.740 --> 00:12:08.240
been?

00:12:08.240 --> 00:12:11.270
And secondly, you've got some
of the smartest YouTube folks

00:12:11.270 --> 00:12:12.470
sitting right here.

00:12:12.470 --> 00:12:14.465
Do you have any ask for them?

00:12:14.465 --> 00:12:15.590
SHILPA SHETTY KUNDRA: Yeah.

00:12:15.590 --> 00:12:17.180
I want to ask them to help me.

00:12:17.180 --> 00:12:18.830
[LAUGHTER]

00:12:18.830 --> 00:12:21.501
GOPI KALLAYIL: What
help do you want?

00:12:21.501 --> 00:12:23.000
SHILPA SHETTY KUNDRA:
Obviously, I'd

00:12:23.000 --> 00:12:26.390
love to hear from you how
I could popularize this.

00:12:26.390 --> 00:12:29.870
And I realize why I think I'm
one of the first celebrities

00:12:29.870 --> 00:12:31.100
to be a YouTuber.

00:12:31.100 --> 00:12:33.200
Because it takes so long.

00:12:33.200 --> 00:12:35.450
It takes so much time.

00:12:35.450 --> 00:12:38.390
You know, we're such a pampered
lot and also spoiled in the way

00:12:38.390 --> 00:12:41.160
that we are paid
for every minute.

00:12:41.160 --> 00:12:43.520
And this is something
that I'm doing free.

00:12:43.520 --> 00:12:47.480
And I'm saying this
with a lot of humility.

00:12:47.480 --> 00:12:53.030
So I realized when I embarked
on this venture or this journey

00:12:53.030 --> 00:12:55.800
that I thought, you
know, I'll just shoot,

00:12:55.800 --> 00:12:57.880
and I'll just start
putting up stuff.

00:12:57.880 --> 00:13:00.720
But it wasn't that easy.

00:13:00.720 --> 00:13:04.390
There was work going into
what we are supposed to shoot,

00:13:04.390 --> 00:13:07.790
what we are supposed
to actually put out,

00:13:07.790 --> 00:13:11.180
targeting all the
important questions.

00:13:11.180 --> 00:13:13.430
As a layman, what is it that--

00:13:13.430 --> 00:13:15.120
how do we start off?

00:13:15.120 --> 00:13:19.616
How do we keep that
interest going?

00:13:19.616 --> 00:13:21.240
What is the first
thing that will catch

00:13:21.240 --> 00:13:25.760
people's eyes or imagination?

00:13:25.760 --> 00:13:27.640
How do we get them
interested in health?

00:13:27.640 --> 00:13:29.480
There was so much homework.

00:13:29.480 --> 00:13:34.527
And then the hours of shooting,
eight hours of doing yoga--

00:13:34.527 --> 00:13:35.360
GOPI KALLAYIL: Yeah.

00:13:35.360 --> 00:13:36.350
In one day?

00:13:36.350 --> 00:13:39.327
SHILPA SHETTY KUNDRA: Eight
hours every shoot of doing--

00:13:39.327 --> 00:13:40.160
you know, six hours.

00:13:40.160 --> 00:13:42.714
I couldn't do beyond that
because I started cramping.

00:13:42.714 --> 00:13:44.630
And you know, when you
do yoga, you can't eat.

00:13:44.630 --> 00:13:45.630
GOPI KALLAYIL: True.

00:13:45.630 --> 00:13:47.088
SHILPA SHETTY
KUNDRA: So I was on--

00:13:47.088 --> 00:13:50.970
I was just sipping
on liquids and fruit.

00:13:50.970 --> 00:13:54.580
So our shoots would begin at,
like, 9:00 in the morning.

00:13:54.580 --> 00:13:56.667
And I'd have to keep light.

00:13:56.667 --> 00:13:59.000
GOPI KALLAYIL: So you were
fully enlightened by evening.

00:13:59.000 --> 00:14:00.041
SHILPA SHETTY KUNDRA: No.

00:14:00.041 --> 00:14:03.320
And the beauty of
it is I discovered--

00:14:03.320 --> 00:14:05.450
I discovered so much
through that journey.

00:14:05.450 --> 00:14:07.100
Because I mean,
when you do yoga,

00:14:07.100 --> 00:14:09.300
you don't do it beyond an hour.

00:14:09.300 --> 00:14:12.170
But at the shoot,
because I, obviously,

00:14:12.170 --> 00:14:15.090
wanted to do my
best, and I wanted

00:14:15.090 --> 00:14:18.810
to do it every
asana to my optimum

00:14:18.810 --> 00:14:24.080
best because I wanted
people to realize that this

00:14:24.080 --> 00:14:27.260
is what you can achieve.

00:14:27.260 --> 00:14:30.290
So I didn't know I had
that kind of strength.

00:14:30.290 --> 00:14:33.140
And I didn't know that
I could actually stay

00:14:33.140 --> 00:14:36.490
without food for six hours.

00:14:36.490 --> 00:14:39.860
And that's the power of yoga.

00:14:39.860 --> 00:14:41.637
It truly is mind over body.

00:14:41.637 --> 00:14:42.720
GOPI KALLAYIL: Absolutely.

00:14:42.720 --> 00:14:45.860
SHILPA SHETTY KUNDRA: And so
till the shoot would go on,

00:14:45.860 --> 00:14:46.515
I'd be OK.

00:14:46.515 --> 00:14:48.860
And as soon as the shoot
was over, I'd be like,

00:14:48.860 --> 00:14:50.930
give me anything to eat!

00:14:50.930 --> 00:14:52.340
So that is amazing.

00:14:52.340 --> 00:14:53.935
And then also with the cooking--

00:14:53.935 --> 00:14:55.310
so we didn't have
a food stylist.

00:14:55.310 --> 00:14:56.660
It's YouTube.

00:14:56.660 --> 00:14:59.030
We had really [INAUDIBLE].

00:14:59.030 --> 00:15:01.220
So we're, like, cost-cutting.

00:15:01.220 --> 00:15:02.390
I said, we can't afford it.

00:15:02.390 --> 00:15:04.070
This is not a normal shoot.

00:15:04.070 --> 00:15:08.510
So everything from cutting
the vegetables to putting it

00:15:08.510 --> 00:15:10.430
on the plate, and
showing it to people,

00:15:10.430 --> 00:15:12.540
I've done it all myself.

00:15:15.680 --> 00:15:19.520
And we did nearly
eight dishes a day

00:15:19.520 --> 00:15:23.380
because we wanted a bank
before we started rolling.

00:15:23.380 --> 00:15:27.890
And the minute we had
60, 70 videos in hand,

00:15:27.890 --> 00:15:29.270
that's when I launched it.

00:15:29.270 --> 00:15:33.660
But the work has been going
on for the last nine months.

00:15:33.660 --> 00:15:35.570
So it was a lot of hard work.

00:15:35.570 --> 00:15:37.040
And that's what I realized.

00:15:37.040 --> 00:15:40.560
And then after you finished
it, I also had to dub it.

00:15:40.560 --> 00:15:44.180
So every asana is dubbed by me.

00:15:44.180 --> 00:15:45.620
So it was a lot of hard work.

00:15:45.620 --> 00:15:48.350
So I realized why no
celebrity wants to do this.

00:15:48.350 --> 00:15:50.314
I was like, good gracious god.

00:15:50.314 --> 00:15:51.980
GOPI KALLAYIL: So
that's great feedback.

00:15:51.980 --> 00:15:52.938
And we'll take it away.

00:15:52.938 --> 00:15:55.930
And we're happy to share
some best practices with you.

00:15:55.930 --> 00:15:58.590
But one suggestion is actually
that behind-the-scene story

00:15:58.590 --> 00:16:00.436
you just told, that
itself will make

00:16:00.436 --> 00:16:01.560
for an interesting episode.

00:16:01.560 --> 00:16:02.935
Because people
want to hear that.

00:16:02.935 --> 00:16:04.290
Your fans want to hear that.

00:16:04.290 --> 00:16:08.130
So go back and relive
the production days--

00:16:08.130 --> 00:16:09.000
one more video.

00:16:09.000 --> 00:16:11.200
[LAUGHTER]

00:16:11.200 --> 00:16:13.217
SHILPA SHETTY
KUNDRA: That's crazy.

00:16:13.217 --> 00:16:14.550
But what did you take out of it?

00:16:14.550 --> 00:16:17.640
I want to know from you because
you are a yogi yourself,

00:16:17.640 --> 00:16:19.477
and you're very passionate.

00:16:19.477 --> 00:16:20.310
GOPI KALLAYIL: Yeah.

00:16:20.310 --> 00:16:23.130
So my biggest takeaway
is, when I was a kid,

00:16:23.130 --> 00:16:25.770
I ran away to an ashram
and I learned yoga.

00:16:25.770 --> 00:16:28.970
And we were primarily taught
by bearded men in orange.

00:16:28.970 --> 00:16:31.530
It was an esoteric practice.

00:16:31.530 --> 00:16:34.140
And thanks to now,
supermodels, super-actresses

00:16:34.140 --> 00:16:37.140
turned super-yoginis,
it's become

00:16:37.140 --> 00:16:40.200
more accessible to
a larger population.

00:16:40.200 --> 00:16:42.000
It's got de-mystified.

00:16:42.000 --> 00:16:46.140
And you frame it in
more contemporary terms.

00:16:46.140 --> 00:16:48.644
And you make it accessible to
a lot of people otherwise who

00:16:48.644 --> 00:16:49.810
would not have looked at it.

00:16:49.810 --> 00:16:51.360
So I want to thank
you for doing it.

00:16:51.360 --> 00:16:51.750
SHILPA SHETTY KUNDRA: How sweet.

00:16:51.750 --> 00:16:52.249
Thank you.

00:16:52.249 --> 00:16:55.160
And I want to thank you that
you're in San Francisco,

00:16:55.160 --> 00:16:59.769
and you're such diligent
follower of yoga.

00:16:59.769 --> 00:17:01.560
And you're trying to
spread the word, which

00:17:01.560 --> 00:17:02.520
is really wonderful.

00:17:02.520 --> 00:17:04.109
So a huge round of
applause for you.

00:17:04.109 --> 00:17:05.150
GOPI KALLAYIL: Thank you.

00:17:05.150 --> 00:17:06.262
[APPLAUSE]

00:17:06.262 --> 00:17:07.640
SHILPA SHETTY KUNDRA: Wonderful.

00:17:07.640 --> 00:17:09.410
GOPI KALLAYIL: So
speaking of yoga,

00:17:09.410 --> 00:17:12.890
one question, and then we'll
go into a practice mode.

00:17:12.890 --> 00:17:16.760
Bollywood is not exactly
the right environment

00:17:16.760 --> 00:17:19.594
for a yoga mindfulness
kind of practice.

00:17:19.594 --> 00:17:20.510
It's a frenzied place.

00:17:20.510 --> 00:17:21.759
Things move quickly.

00:17:21.759 --> 00:17:24.300
And there's a lot of tension
and stress, and a lot of travel.

00:17:24.300 --> 00:17:26.300
So how do you reconcile
those two worlds

00:17:26.300 --> 00:17:28.250
and bring it together?

00:17:28.250 --> 00:17:30.710
SHILPA SHETTY KUNDRA: That's
a really interesting question.

00:17:30.710 --> 00:17:32.540
That's why I'm not
doing movies right now.

00:17:32.540 --> 00:17:37.720
[LAUGHS] I haven't done
for the last seven years.

00:17:37.720 --> 00:17:40.160
I think maybe nine.

00:17:40.160 --> 00:17:41.760
But I'm still here.

00:17:41.760 --> 00:17:43.430
I'm still at Google.

00:17:43.430 --> 00:17:46.040
And I've made my choices.

00:17:46.040 --> 00:17:47.305
I've been there, done that.

00:17:47.305 --> 00:17:51.960
I've been part of the milieu
for the last 20 years.

00:17:51.960 --> 00:17:53.420
I do TV.

00:17:53.420 --> 00:17:55.610
I choose to do that
because I can't be part

00:17:55.610 --> 00:18:02.600
of this erratic timings and--

00:18:02.600 --> 00:18:05.480
I have a
4-and-1/2-year-old baby.

00:18:05.480 --> 00:18:08.750
And for me, I'm very
clear that that is my--

00:18:08.750 --> 00:18:09.960
he is my priority.

00:18:09.960 --> 00:18:12.370
My family is my first priority.

00:18:12.370 --> 00:18:17.150
And I want to give time to
myself, and unapologetically.

00:18:17.150 --> 00:18:20.780
And when you're an actor,
it's very hard to do that.

00:18:20.780 --> 00:18:22.700
So I mean, obviously,
my recognition

00:18:22.700 --> 00:18:24.230
comes through movies.

00:18:24.230 --> 00:18:26.480
That will always be
my claim to fame.

00:18:26.480 --> 00:18:28.730
I'm very proud of it.

00:18:28.730 --> 00:18:31.610
But if I do choose
to do a movie,

00:18:31.610 --> 00:18:33.560
I'll have to work
around my schedules.

00:18:33.560 --> 00:18:37.520
It'll have to be a film that
will start and end quickly.

00:18:37.520 --> 00:18:41.810
Also, I think I don't do yoga
because of the frenzied life

00:18:41.810 --> 00:18:43.060
that we lead.

00:18:45.670 --> 00:18:47.360
It's a very hard life.

00:18:47.360 --> 00:18:49.730
You're constantly living
in a glass fishbowl.

00:18:49.730 --> 00:18:52.845
And you're getting trolled.

00:18:55.970 --> 00:18:59.750
Instagram determines how famous
you are, how much you're liked.

00:19:02.350 --> 00:19:03.260
It's really shallow.

00:19:05.900 --> 00:19:10.970
Though I have to say in the
most unhypocritical sort of way,

00:19:10.970 --> 00:19:12.530
that I love that.

00:19:12.530 --> 00:19:13.650
I love it.

00:19:13.650 --> 00:19:15.950
I really do.

00:19:15.950 --> 00:19:19.790
But the time that I
share with myself,

00:19:19.790 --> 00:19:26.101
that, for me, is just my time.

00:19:26.101 --> 00:19:26.600
You know?

00:19:26.600 --> 00:19:29.310
It just helps me
cope with everything.

00:19:29.310 --> 00:19:35.840
So even if I'm trolled, and if
somebody writes a bad article,

00:19:35.840 --> 00:19:37.580
that's part of my life.

00:19:37.580 --> 00:19:39.770
The morning that I wake
up, and I do my pranayama,

00:19:39.770 --> 00:19:44.600
and I'm in the sun, basking in
its glory, and my feet are--

00:19:44.600 --> 00:19:49.340
my feet is firmly on
the grass, that is life.

00:19:49.340 --> 00:19:50.620
You know?

00:19:50.620 --> 00:19:55.610
Just being able to do
that, to breathe the air

00:19:55.610 --> 00:19:59.060
and to just live this
blessed life, for me,

00:19:59.060 --> 00:20:07.470
that is far more important than
all the craziness of our job.

00:20:07.470 --> 00:20:09.200
So I think that's what
keeps me grounded.

00:20:09.200 --> 00:20:10.790
So a lot of people
tell me, how do you

00:20:10.790 --> 00:20:15.080
manage to be so positive?

00:20:15.080 --> 00:20:18.400
And you're, like, smiling.

00:20:18.400 --> 00:20:19.760
I get upset.

00:20:19.760 --> 00:20:21.890
I'm only human.

00:20:21.890 --> 00:20:23.150
Of course, I get upset.

00:20:23.150 --> 00:20:28.520
Of course, I go through
my times of why would they

00:20:28.520 --> 00:20:29.610
write something like that?

00:20:29.610 --> 00:20:31.070
But then I'm out of it.

00:20:31.070 --> 00:20:32.190
I don't carry forward.

00:20:32.190 --> 00:20:35.380
And I think yoga has
helped me do that.

00:20:35.380 --> 00:20:41.940
Yoga has made me believe that
what cannot be cured has to be

00:20:41.940 --> 00:20:43.550
endured.

00:20:43.550 --> 00:20:50.750
And once you understand that,
life is so much more easier.

00:20:50.750 --> 00:20:52.920
Otherwise, being an actor
is a really hard job.

00:20:52.920 --> 00:20:54.570
Let me tell you.

00:20:54.570 --> 00:20:58.220
And to be part of it for
the last 23 years has been--

00:20:58.220 --> 00:20:58.970
I don't know how--

00:20:58.970 --> 00:21:00.678
I don't know how I've
lasted out so long.

