00:23:46.150 --> 00:23:48.220
What is pranayama?

00:23:48.220 --> 00:23:51.220
Most importantly, before we
start, for all those people

00:23:51.220 --> 00:23:55.060
who don't know the
meaning of pranayama,

00:23:55.060 --> 00:23:58.630
"prana" means "life."

00:23:58.630 --> 00:24:04.480
And "yama" means "control."

00:24:04.480 --> 00:24:10.540
So the god of death is called
Yama because he controls life.

00:24:10.540 --> 00:24:18.430
So pranayama actually is the
control of your life force,

00:24:18.430 --> 00:24:21.940
which happens through breath.

00:24:21.940 --> 00:24:26.230
So when they say
align your breath,

00:24:26.230 --> 00:24:30.700
you are controlling
your mind through that.

00:24:30.700 --> 00:24:33.580
And when your mind
is in control,

00:24:33.580 --> 00:24:39.280
there's nothing that you
cannot achieve in life.

00:24:39.280 --> 00:24:43.570
So most importantly, why we
lead such fast-paced lives,

00:24:43.570 --> 00:24:49.090
even if we don't get the
time to do all the asanas,

00:24:49.090 --> 00:24:51.800
if we just get the time to
just do a few pranayamas.

00:24:54.400 --> 00:24:57.900
It takes 10 minutes.

00:24:57.900 --> 00:25:03.530
And if 10 minutes can actually
align your mind, body,

00:25:03.530 --> 00:25:09.100
and soul, life would
be so worth living.

00:25:09.100 --> 00:25:11.860
So we'll start off with
the simple technique

00:25:11.860 --> 00:25:16.480
of just inhaling and
exhaling through your nose.

00:25:16.480 --> 00:25:17.860
OK?

00:25:17.860 --> 00:25:21.910
When you inhale, let
your chest open out.

00:25:21.910 --> 00:25:24.160
OK?

00:25:24.160 --> 00:25:25.790
OK?

00:25:25.790 --> 00:25:29.170
In dhyana mudra.

00:25:29.170 --> 00:25:32.710
They say this is
the mudra of wisdom.

00:25:32.710 --> 00:25:36.590
Your heart and your
mind are aligned.

00:25:36.590 --> 00:25:37.480
On your knees.

00:25:40.630 --> 00:25:42.198
Taking a deep breath.

00:25:42.198 --> 00:25:43.572
[INHALES]

00:25:46.780 --> 00:25:48.572
Exhale.

00:25:48.572 --> 00:25:54.614
[EXHALES DEEPLY] Deep breath in.

00:25:54.614 --> 00:25:56.934
[INHALES DEEPLY]

00:25:58.790 --> 00:25:59.561
Exhale.

00:25:59.561 --> 00:26:02.858
[EXHALES DEEPLY]

00:26:04.280 --> 00:26:05.180
Once more.

00:26:05.180 --> 00:26:12.026
[INHALES DEEPLY]
[EXHALES DEEPLY]

00:26:19.870 --> 00:26:23.140
Wonderful.

00:26:23.140 --> 00:26:26.980
We start off with Anulom Vilum,
where we take in the breath

00:26:26.980 --> 00:26:29.260
through the left nostril.

00:26:29.260 --> 00:26:30.190
OK?

00:26:30.190 --> 00:26:31.630
So this is your hand.

00:26:31.630 --> 00:26:33.820
Just keep it simple.

00:26:33.820 --> 00:26:34.499
OK?

00:26:34.499 --> 00:26:36.290
There's a more complicated
way of doing it.

00:26:36.290 --> 00:26:37.998
I'm going to keep it
simple for you guys.

00:26:37.998 --> 00:26:39.580
Just the index finger out.

00:26:39.580 --> 00:26:40.416
All right?

00:26:40.416 --> 00:26:43.630
The thumb, OK?

00:26:43.630 --> 00:26:45.280
Or you can even do this.

00:26:45.280 --> 00:26:50.470
So you basically need
to control your thumb

00:26:50.470 --> 00:26:54.580
on your right nostril,
breath in through your left.

00:26:54.580 --> 00:26:56.190
I'll do it once for you.

00:26:56.190 --> 00:26:56.690
OK?

00:26:56.690 --> 00:26:59.190
[INHALES]

00:27:01.690 --> 00:27:04.190
[EXHALES]

00:27:04.190 --> 00:27:06.640
Exhale through the right.

00:27:06.640 --> 00:27:08.440
Then you inhale again
through the right.

00:27:08.440 --> 00:27:17.390
[INHALES] [EXHALES]
Exhale through the left.

00:27:17.390 --> 00:27:18.560
Inhale through the left.

00:27:18.560 --> 00:27:21.482
[INHALES]

00:27:23.430 --> 00:27:25.380
[EXHALES]

00:27:25.380 --> 00:27:27.790
Exhale through the right.

00:27:27.790 --> 00:27:28.765
Get that?

00:27:28.765 --> 00:27:31.550
So this is Anulom Vilum.

00:27:31.550 --> 00:27:32.210
We'll start.

00:27:32.210 --> 00:27:32.710
OK?

00:27:32.710 --> 00:27:34.155
We do five of these.

00:27:34.155 --> 00:27:35.930
All right?

