00:31:07.789 --> 00:31:11.950
It helps you concentrate.

00:31:11.950 --> 00:31:14.680
And the sahasrara chakra,
which is right above that

00:31:14.680 --> 00:31:15.940
in the center of your head.

00:31:22.000 --> 00:31:22.915
Open up your mind.

00:31:27.870 --> 00:31:28.760
And just breathe.

00:31:48.660 --> 00:31:49.806
Open your eyes slowly.

00:31:54.570 --> 00:31:56.650
And now we do Kapalbhati.

00:32:00.080 --> 00:32:02.540
Gopi-ji is going to explain
the method of Kapalbhati

00:32:02.540 --> 00:32:04.715
to you because he's
done many classes.

00:32:07.510 --> 00:32:08.470
Basically-- yeah.

00:32:08.470 --> 00:32:10.178
GOPI KALLAYIL: It's
a breathing technique

00:32:10.178 --> 00:32:14.190
where you pump your lungs
up by forcefully exhaling

00:32:14.190 --> 00:32:16.405
and let the inhalation
come in naturally.

00:32:16.405 --> 00:32:19.294
So one way to get the feel
is to place your right hand

00:32:19.294 --> 00:32:20.660
on your abdomen.

00:32:20.660 --> 00:32:24.264
And exhale forcefully,
and just relax.

00:32:24.264 --> 00:32:27.060
So the exhalation is forced.

00:32:27.060 --> 00:32:30.280
The inhalation, you just
let it naturally come.

00:32:30.280 --> 00:32:32.182
Then you do a series
of them like this.

00:32:32.182 --> 00:32:33.660
SHILPA SHETTY KUNDRA:
Shall we do sets of 20?

00:32:33.660 --> 00:32:34.440
GOPI KALLAYIL: OK.

00:32:34.440 --> 00:32:36.356
SHILPA SHETTY KUNDRA:
We'll do two sets of 20.

00:32:36.356 --> 00:32:40.350
You have to imagine, what
if a small little insect

00:32:40.350 --> 00:32:41.907
has gone into your nose?

00:32:41.907 --> 00:32:42.990
How would you take it out?

00:32:42.990 --> 00:32:46.570
[EXHALES SEVERAL TIMES]
Yeah, that's

00:32:46.570 --> 00:32:47.680
one way of explaining it.

00:32:47.680 --> 00:32:48.430
GOPI KALLAYIL: 20.

00:32:48.430 --> 00:32:49.555
SHILPA SHETTY KUNDRA: Yeah.

00:32:49.555 --> 00:32:51.050
For people who've
never known yoga.

00:32:51.050 --> 00:32:52.508
GOPI KALLAYIL: Blow
out 20 insects.

00:32:52.508 --> 00:32:54.590
SHILPA SHETTY KUNDRA:
Yeah, blow out 20 insects.

00:32:54.590 --> 00:33:03.070
And you have to feel the air
be pumped from the center.

00:33:03.070 --> 00:33:04.780
OK?

00:33:04.780 --> 00:33:06.970
And what this
technique does, it's

00:33:06.970 --> 00:33:10.330
a brain cleansing technique.

00:33:10.330 --> 00:33:12.940
It's a very, very
powerful technique

00:33:12.940 --> 00:33:16.110
and a powerful pranayama.

00:33:16.110 --> 00:33:20.500
So we start, hands on your--

00:33:20.500 --> 00:33:24.200
one hand on your
navel, the center.

00:33:24.200 --> 00:33:26.590
Yeah?

00:33:26.590 --> 00:33:28.102
Take a deep breath in.

00:33:28.102 --> 00:33:30.994
[INHALES]

